issue.body:
ThrowsConstraint behaves differently depending on whether the exception is thrown directly by the method under test or returned as part of the resulting Task.

``` csharp
[TestFixture]
public class TestFixture
{
  [Test]
  public void TestFails()
  {
    Assert.That(() => ThrowsDirectly(), Throws.TypeOf<InvalidOperationException>());
  }

  [Test]
  public void TestSucceeds()
  {
    Assert.That(() => ThrowsAsync(), Throws.TypeOf<InvalidOperationException>());
  }

  private Task ThrowsDirectly()
  {
    throw new InvalidOperationException();
  }

  private async Task ThrowsAsync()
  {
    await Task.Yield();
    throw new InvalidOperationException();
  }
}
```
